main event: A single witness observed five unidentified objects in Mobile, Alabama on May 25, 1966, for a duration of 50 minutes.
interesting points: The objects appeared in conjunction with five white clouds that had a pink cast., The sighting was reported under typical atmospheric conditions such as scattered clouds and light wind., The moon was not visible during the sighting but became visible afterwards., The objects were described as flat and saucer-like, yellowish-white in color., A previous sighting of a similar nature was reported in the same location about a year prior.
witness description: The observer noted the objects' appearance and environmental conditions during the sighting.
